Get a Summary of a User’s Permissions and Access
If you've wondered what permissions, public groups, or queues a user is assigned, you're in luck. With the User Access Summary you can see this information directly from the user’s detail page, saving you time, clicks, and effort.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) in all editions.
How: From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Users, and then select Users. Select a user, and then click View Summary.
